De_Heavens takes you to a world in pieces, literally. A castle sprawling across floating blocks, with a small village developed around it.A peaceful, magical world no doubt, But alas, this world is not perfect for all. A bunch of terrorists have decided to demonstrate their contempt by exploding the castle. As this plot unfolds, a group of villagers, well equipped with anti-terrorism equipment have decided to stop them. Both sides now fight to establish their beliefs in the skies.

de_haywire_beta - May 16 2005 - Visit www.DreamServers.ro
================================================================
Title                   : de_haywire
Filenames               : de_haywire.txt (this readme file)
                          de_haywire.nav (bot file)
                          de_haywire.bsp (the level itself)
                          plus 4 screenshots (in \screenshots)

Author                  : The LoveMeister
Email Address           : lovemeister@panzer.dk
Web Page		: :(
Description             : DE map for 8-20 players ideally,
                          3 routes, 2 sites
================================================================

* Play Information *

New Sounds              : no
New Graphics            : no
New Music               : no

* Construction *

Base                    : new level from scratch
Editor(s) used          : 3ds MAX 7, the GLB exporter and Hammer
Known Bugs              : it's possible to buddy jump out of the
			  map pretty much everywhere, so please 
			  don't try : ). The bots are a bit funky 
			  sometimes
Build Time              : two weeks on and off
Compile machine         : p4, 2.4GHz, 512mb ram
Compile Time            : 2:47 seconds

Summary of the level
====================

The map layout is fairly simple and compact with one main area 
and 2 alternative routes. There are no really dark spots for
camping nor are there any sniper killing zones. All the good sniper
spots have at least one dead angle making them difficult to hold.
Yet it is still possible to use scoped weapons to great effect.
I've also made some fairly confined areas for those of you who 
prefer the shotty : ).

To do for next version
======================
Currently there are no ambient sounds in the map. That has a main 
priority for the next release. I would also like to add some more
'clutter' to the map in general. 
The most important ofcourse is all the tweaks to the map itself
based on player feedback : ).


Shoutout's
==========
Slick_oh and Flum for playtest, suggestions and interest 
Rich McNinch for Hammer/Source help - really appreciated
Whoever came up with the idea to make the source WIKI : )
*** http://www.hl2world.com/wiki/index.php/Main_Page ***
Support the wiki initiative!
================================================================

The LoveMeister

FOREWORD:
An unprofessional map created by me. This is actually my first real map, so i decided to "release" it (you gotta start with something anyway).

CONTENT:
Basically, this is a not too big bomb defuse map. Each side (T and CT) starts in a house, located on an open area, separated by a tall wall. They must both make their way to the bomb site first.

FEATURES:
This map has realistic lighting. It contain some static and moveable props, as well as breakable glass and ladders.

CREDITS:
All credit goes to me. I made this map on my own, and when i gain more experience in mapping, i will form a group to make bigger an better maps.

NOTE:
If you have any tips, comments,... feel free to tell me! You will help me in making better maps.

This is a beta, and it is very much still in progress.  I'm just releasing it as a beta for now despite several known issues.  THESE ISSUES ARE:

The VIS would not run, bots cannot use this map because the .nav cannot run thanks to an unknown issue in the map.

The fog in the pictures had to be taken out, it caused a problem with the muzzleflash but it'll be worked on.

These issues might not seem like much, but without the VIS running, bots are useless and lag is abundant.

**IMPORTANT** If any other map makers wish to help finalize this map and are willing to fix the VIS bug and fog issues, please download and use VMEX to decompile it into a hammer file that can be edited as such.  If you do make a finalized edit, send me a message and reupload the map under the same name excluding the beta part.  Please put me down as a main author and yourself as whatever part you wish.  DO NOT add a bunch of new areas, entities, or other things that will make the map too different from what it is now!  Have fun!

de_guard map for CS:S is a port of the de_guard map from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

Unfortunately, the Map has a low fps, because the author forgot to optimize the Map.

Map script

A new restaurant is opening in the Czech city, and Lord Uilayam himself was invited to open it.

But the terrorists are going to blow up the beer delivery truck to ruin everyone's holiday.

The map was created by Austrian player poLemin alone. It was added to the workshop on September 27 at 14:18, even then it was possible to try it.

During this time, the map received 6 updates, which allowed it to become one of the new map operations.

Appearance of map

The map does not stand out for its beauty from the rest, but it is pleasing to the eye.

Nice lighting, no acid colors, no unnecessary details that will reduce the fps.

As if he was in the Czech Republic, among their age-old architecture.

Geometry of map

Since the map was created for the “partners” mode, it is quite small in size. It is quite easy to navigate on it after 5 minutes of the game. On the sides there are two paths to the site, and a small balcony from which you can fall directly to the point of the bookmark.

Game strategy

CT can be squeezed in the back through the tunnel, so you should be on the watch.

When entering the site, check the sand and the water

When entering the shorts, check under the stairs, because there may be a CT

When playing as a CT, do not be afraid to press your opponents, there are many opportunities for such a maneuver on the map

Throw hammers on the car, because there often sits kt.
